South Africa Stocks Fall for Second Day, Led by Anglo American

-- B y   R o b e r t   B r a n d
-- 
2011-03-28T07:58:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-28/south-africa-stocks-fall-for-second-day-led-by-anglo-american.html
South African stocks fell for a
second day, led by  Anglo American Plc (AGL) , the miner that makes up
11 percent of the benchmark index, after metals including copper
and platinum retreated.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index dropped as much as 0.8
percent, and traded 0.5 percent down at 31,430.81 by 9:52 a.m.
in Johannesburg. Anglo American, part owner of the worldâ€™s
biggest platinum producer, declined as much as 1.4 percent to
347.23 rand.  The price of platinum slid 1 percent. Copper slumped 1.4
percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
